<p class="p">Reactions occurring between the phosphatizing solution and metal surface are shown in 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="materials-11-02585-f001" class="xref">Figure 1</xref>. At the beginning of the process, a dissociation of H
 <sub class="sub">3</sub>PO
 <sub class="sub">4</sub> into H
 <sub class="sub">2</sub>PO
 <sub class="sub">4</sub>
 <sup class="sup">−</sup> ion between pH 1 to 3 takes place (Equation (3)) [
 <xref rid="B30-materials-11-02585" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">30</xref>]. 
 <disp-formula class="disp-formula">H
  <sub class="sub">3</sub>PO
  <sub class="sub">4</sub> → H
  <sub class="sub">2</sub>PO
  <sub class="sub">4</sub>
  <sup class="sup">−</sup> + H
  <sup class="sup">+</sup>
  <label class="label">(3)</label>
 </disp-formula>
 <disp-formula class="disp-formula">3Mn
  <sup class="sup">2+</sup> + 2H
  <sub class="sub">2</sub>PO
  <sub class="sub">4</sub>
  <sup class="sup">−</sup> → Mn
  <sub class="sub">3</sub>(PO
  <sub class="sub">4</sub>)
  <sub class="sub">2</sub> + 4H
  <sup class="sup">+</sup>
  <label class="label">(4)</label>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
